          <div class="oss-text">
            <p>Linux, Ubuntu, and Budgie desktop are all Open Source — software that can be freely used, changed, and shared by anyone. Ubuntu Budgie is free in the truest sense of the word.</p>
            <p>The licence allows anyone to use Linux for any purpose, distribute it, modify it, redistribute it, or even sell it. If you make improvements, you are encouraged to contribute them back for possible inclusion in future versions.</p>
            <p>Linux is supported not by one company, but by an entire ecosystem. <a href="https://www.linuxfoundation.org/news-media/infographics/who-writes-linux-2015">Over 4,000 developers have contributed</a> to Linux in the last 15 years, backed by:</p>
